    The current `notekit` tree is small and the merged checklist and summary features both pass their targeted tests, but the package surface and the implementation quality have not been brought back into sync after the merges. The two new modules are only reachable through direct module imports, the same whitespace-normalization logic now exists in three places, and the summary builder still allows malformed markdown when the title normalizes to an empty string.
    
    ## Required Changes
    
    - Export the merged feature APIs from the package root in `src/notekit/__init__.py` so callers can import `render_checklist` and `build_summary` the same way they already import `normalize_note`. Right now the merged branches added `src/notekit/checklist.py` and `src/notekit/summary.py`, but `__all__` still exposes only `normalize_note`, which leaves the package interface incomplete after the feature merges.
    - Remove the duplicated `" ".join(...split())` normalization code from `src/notekit/checklist.py` and `src/notekit/summary.py` by reusing `normalize_note()` from `src/notekit/text.py` or a shared internal helper. The current duplication means any future change to note normalization rules has to be made in three separate functions and can easily drift.
    - Harden `build_summary()` in `src/notekit/summary.py` for empty normalized titles and empty line lists. As written, `build_summary("   ", ["first"])` returns `## \n- first`, and `build_summary("   ", [])` returns `## `. Add explicit validation or a defined fallback so the function cannot emit a blank markdown heading.
    
    ## Nice to Have
    
    - Expand `README.md` beyond the one-line project description so it documents the currently available helpers and shows the supported import style. The repository now has three public behaviors, but the root documentation still reflects only the initial seed project.
